  "architecture_summary": "Swin Transformer V2 adapts the original Swin Transformer with residual post-normalization, scaled cosine attention, and log-spaced continuous position bias to scale model capacity and window resolution more effectively. It also uses SimMIM self-supervised pre-training and memory-saving implementations such as ZeRO, activation check-pointing, and sequential self-attention computation to train models up to 3 billion parameters.",
